{"metrics":{"latencyMs":2550},"output":{"message":{"content":[{"text":"Based on the search results and current date information:\n\n**Current Date:** March 15, 2026\n\n**CVE-2020-10188 Exploits:**\nCVE-2020-10188 is a **buffer overflow vulnerability in telnetd** (the telnet daemon). This is a critical remote code execution vulnerability that affects various telnet server implementations. \n\nBuffer overflow vulnerabilities like this one allow attackers to:\n- Execute arbitrary code on the affected system\n- Gain unauthorized access to the system\n- Potentially take complete control of the affected host\n\n**Important Notes:**\n- This is an older vulnerability (from 2020) and patches should be available\n- Systems running vulnerable versions of telnet daemons are at risk\n- If you're managing systems, ensure telnetd is updated or consider using more secure alternatives like SSH instead of Telnet\n- Telnet itself is considered insecure and should not be used in production environments anymore\n\nIf you need more specific information about exploitation techniques, proof-of-concept code, or affected software versions, please let me know and I can search for more detailed information."}],"role":"assistant"}},"stopReason":"end_turn","usage":{"cacheReadInputTokenCount":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheWriteInputTokenCount":0,"cacheWriteInputTokens":0,"inputTokens":810,"outputTokens":247,"serverToolUsage":{},"totalTokens":1057}}1439 1231
